     <body>
     <div type="encomium">
   <head>On my Friend and adopted sonne M<seg rend="sup">r</seg>. Thomas
Iordan the Infant-Poet of our Age.</head>
   <l>FRom smallest Springs, arise the greatest streames,</l>
   <l>Thou hast begun well; who dares hinder thee</l>
   <l>Still to goe forward, and dilate thy beames,</l>
   <l>T'acquaint the world with thy sweete Poetry.</l>
   <l>Speake still in <hi>tune,</hi> hide not thy worth but shew it,</l>
   <l>That <hi>men</hi> may say, th'art <hi>borne</hi> not <hi>made</hi> a Poe<gap reason="illegible" resp="#tech" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>.</l>
   <l>And he that fayles thy growing Muse to cherish,</l>
   <l>May his fixt hopes in expectation perish.</l>
   <l>Thine <hi>(sance Complement)</hi>
   </l>
   <closer>
      <signed>I. B.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
